node.title: Live: Case numbers for past 48 hours incoming, more locations of interest info released for Mt Maunganui festival
node.content: ["New Zealand's latest COVID-19 case numbers for the past 48 hours are due on Sunday afternoon as New Year's Eve parties and summer festivals continue to be added as locations of interest.\u00a0", "So far, the Britomart Block Party, a drum and bass festival in Mt Maunganui and the Hidden Valley Festival in Matakana have been added.", "Two cases in Wellington are possibly linked to the Mt Maunganui festival.", "The Ministry of Health didn't release COVID-19 numbers on Saturday, meaning the number released on Sunday will represent two days' worth of new infections.", "11:45am - Kia ora and welcome to Newshub's live COVID updates for Sunday, January 9.", "There are several new locations of interest that have been released so far today, including more information for the drum and bass festival in Mt Maunganui.
